        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 15 at 6:03PM CDT until May 15 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hillcrest, or 7
miles northwest of Rochelle, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Oregon, Lost Nation, Monroe Center, Lindenwood, Hillcrest, Davis
Junction, Kings, Stillman Valley, Chana, Grand Detour, Byron, and
Rochelle.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for north central
Illinois. A Tornado Watch also remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT
for north central Illinois.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
